Package gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.segment

Class ORCParser

java.lang.Object
gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.segment.AbstractStructureParser
gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.segment.AbstractSegmentParser
gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.segment.ORCParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
Processor<ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.Message,ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.Segment>
@Produces(segment="ORC", resource=org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.ServiceRequest.class, extra={org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Practitioner.class,org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Organization.class,org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Immunization.class}) public class ORCParser extends AbstractSegmentParser
ORCParser parses any ORC segments in a message to a ServiceRequest If the message is a VXU or an response to an immunization query, it also produces an Immunization resource.
Author:
Audacious Inquiry

      protected List<FieldHandler> getFieldHandlers()
      Description copied from class: AbstractStructureParser
      Subclasses must implement this method to get the field handlers. The list of field handers can be stored as a static member of the Parser class, and initialized once from a concrete instance of that class using initFieldHandlers.
